                    <br>
                    <p>The electricity bill calculator built with VBA in Microsoft Excel likely automates the process of
                        calculating electricity usage costs based on data inputs like usage (in kWh), rate per unit, and
                        other relevant factors (such as taxes or additional fees). Users input their usage data, and
                        your program automatically generates a detailed bill that includes the total cost, breakdowns of
                        charges, and potentially a summary of usage. VBA (Visual Basic for Applications) allows for such
                        automation, enabling you to create forms, generate reports, and process data efficiently within
                        the familiar Excel interface.</p>
                    <br>
